,{"title":"Author/Maria Scuto","target":"Author/Maria Scuto","line":101},{"title":"Author/Maria Laura Ontario","target":"Author/Maria Laura Ontario","line":102},{"title":"Author/Maria Laura Ontario","target":"Author/Maria Laura Ontario","line":103},{"title":"Author/Salvatore Cuzzocrea","target":"Author/Salvatore Cuzzocrea","line":104},{"title":"Author/Salvatore Cuzzocrea","target":"Author/Salvatore Cuzzocrea","line":105},{"title":"Author/Rosanna Di Paola","target":"Author/Rosanna Di Paola","line":106},{"title":"Author/Rosanna Di Paola","target":"Author/Rosanna Di Paola","line":107},{"title":"Author/Antonella Petrillo","target":"Author/Antonella Petrillo","line":108},{"title":"Author/Roberta Fusco","target":"Author/Roberta Fusco","line":109},{"title":"Author/Roberta Fusco","target":"Author/Roberta Fusco","line":110},{"title":"Author/Vittorio Calabrese","target":"Author/Vittorio Calabrese","line":111},{"title":"Author/Vittorio Calabrese","target":"Author/Vittorio Calabrese","line":112},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/cordaro_key_2021/cordaro_key_2021.pdf","line":114}],"metadata":{"id":"cordaro_key_2021","type":"article-journal","title":"Key Mechanisms and Potential Implications of Hericium erinaceus in NLRP3 Inflammasome Activation by Reactive Oxygen Species during Alzheimer’s Disease","issued":{"date-parts":[[2021]]},"DOI":"10.3390/antiox10111664","container-title":"Antioxidants","abstract":"Alzheimer’s disease (AD) is the principal cause of dementia, and its incidence increases with age. Altered antioxidant systems and inflammation have an important role in the etiology of neurodegenerative disorders. In this study, we evaluated the effects of Hericium erinaceus, a nutritional mushroom with important antioxidant effects, in a rat model of AD. Animals were injected with 70 mg/Kg of AlCl3 daily for 6 weeks, and Hericium erinaceus was administered daily by gavage. Before the experiment’s end date, behavioral test training was performed. At the end of the study, behavioral changes were assessed, and the animals were euthanized. Brain tissues were harvested for further analysis. AlCl3 mainly accumulates in the hippocampus, the principal region of the brain involved in memory functions and learning. Hericium erinaceus administration reduced behavioral changes and hippocampal neuronal degeneration. Additionally, it reduced phosphorylated Tau levels, aberrant APP overexpression, and β-amyloid accumulation. Moreover, Hericium erinaceus decreased the pro-oxidative and pro-inflammatory hippocampal alterations induced by AD. In particular, it reduced the activation of the NLRP3 inflammasome components, usually activated by increased oxidative stress during AD. Collectively, our results showed that Hericium erinaceus has protective effects on behavioral alteration and histological modification associated with AD due to the modulation of the oxidative and inflammatory pathways, as well as regulating cellular brain stress.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Cordaro","given":"Marika","literal":""},{"family":"Cordaro","given":"Marika","literal":""},{"family":"Salinaro","given":"Angela Trovato","literal":""},{"family":"Salinaro","given":"Angela Trovato","literal":""},{"family":"Siracusa","given":"Rosalba","literal":""},{"family":"Siracusa","given":"Rosalba","literal":""},{"family":"D’Amico","given":"Ramona","literal":""},{"family":"D'Amico","given":"Ramona","literal":""},{"family":"Impellizzeri","given":"Daniela","literal":""},{"family":"Impellizzeri","given":"Daniela","literal":""},{"family":"Scuto","given":"Maria","literal":""},{"family":"Scuto","given":"Maria","literal":""},{"family":"Ontario","given":"Maria Laura","literal":""},{"family":"Ontario","given":"Maria Laura","literal":""},{"family":"Cuzzocrea","given":"Salvatore","literal":""},{"family":"Cuzzocrea","given":"Salvatore","literal":""},{"family":"Paola","given":"Rosanna Di","literal":""},{"family":"Paola","given":"Rosanna Di","literal":""},{"family":"Petrillo","given":"Antonella","literal":""},{"family":"Fusco","given":"Roberta","literal":""},{"family":"Fusco","given":"Roberta","literal":""},{"family":"Calabrese","given":"Vittorio","literal":""},{"family":"Calabrese","given":"Vittorio","literal":""}],"citation-key":"cordaro_key_2021","year":"2021","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Key Mechanisms and Potential Implications of Hericium erinaceus in NLRP3 Inflammasome Activation by Reactive Oxygen Species during Alzheimer’s Disease"],"author-links":["[[Author/Marika Cordaro]]","[[Author/Marika Cordaro]]","[[Author/Angela Trovato Salinaro]]","[[Author/Angela Trovato Salinaro]]","[[Author/Rosalba Siracusa]]","[[Author/Rosalba Siracusa]]","[[Author/Ramona D’Amico]]","[[Author/Ramona D'Amico]]","[[Author/Daniela Impellizzeri]]","[[Author/Daniela Impellizzeri]]","[[Author/Maria Scuto]]","[[Author/Maria Scuto]]","[[Author/Maria Laura Ontario]]","[[Author/Maria Laura Ontario]]","[[Author/Salvatore Cuzzocrea]]","[[Author/Salvatore Cuzzocrea]]","[[Author/Rosanna Di Paola]]","[[Author/Rosanna Di Paola]]","[[Author/Antonella Petrillo]]","[[Author/Roberta Fusco]]","[[Author/Roberta Fusco]]","[[Author/Vittorio Calabrese]]","[[Author/Vittorio Calabrese]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/cordaro_key_2021/cordaro_key_2021.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"misfp","at":1774951892777}},"smart_blocks:Research/@cordaro_key_2021.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[0.01033021,-0.02642129,0.03305395,0.03342208,0.0077325,0.03648292,0.02494693,0.04164426,-0.02493686,-0.06385861,0.00344389,-0.0417887,0.02886494,0.02338006,0.01973494,-0.02032353,-0.06849704,0.02004075,-0.10034262,0.01373094,0.03427712,-0.02526728,0.02865671,0.03091934,-0.01760204,0.05313631,-0.02362602,0.0113028,-0.07920422,-0.21124369,-0.01815902,-0.02909266,0.01403818,-0.03338843,-0.0250245,-0.00199662,-0.02431602,0.02875219,-0.04232271,-0.02930271,0.0722205